Iran’s Khatibi Says Energy Minister Namjou Responsible for OPEC Presidency

-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 
2011-05-15T06:22:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/iran-s-khatibi-says-energy-minister-namjou-responsible-for-opec-presidency.html
Iranian OPEC Governor Mohammad Ali
said his country’s energy minister would be temporarily
responsible for  Iran ’s presidency of the oil exporters’ group.  Energy Minister Majid Namjou’s role as head of Iran’s newly
merged oil and energy ministries means he will also assume the
nation’s current role as president of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries, Khatibi said today in a telephone
interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
